Mike ZafirovskiCEO/ Founder/ Board memberLocationGreater Chicago AreaIndustryVenture Capital & Private EquityCurrentThe Zaf Group, The Blackstone Group, BoeingPreviousNortel Networks, Motorola, GE LightingEducationEdinboro University of Pennsylvania500+ connectionsView Mike’s full profile. It's free!Your colleagues, classmates, and 500 million other professionals are on LinkedIn.View Mike’s Full ProfileSummaryMike Zafirovski is founder/ president of The Zaf Group, a management consulting and investment firm. The Blackstone Group is the firm's principal client where Mike is an executive advisor and also serves on the board of directors of three Blackstone companies:  non-executive chairman of DJO Global Inc and PGI Inc, and independent director for Apria Healthcare Services. Mike also serves on the board of directors of Boeing and Stericycle.Previously, in a 34-year corporate career, he  served 21 years as President/CEO/COO at Nortel, Motorola, and five GE businesses in the high tech, industrial, consumer, and financial services industries. Demonstrated ability to develop strategy, simplify complexity, attract and develop strong teams, and drive execution (in the 21 years of P&L responsibility, revenue growth exceeded 8% per year and EBITDA gains averaged 350 BPs per year).  Among his philanthropic activities, he is vice chairman and leads the strategy committee for AUSL, the organization that helps turnaround the most challenged public schools in Chicago. He is a visiting lecturer at the Northwestern Kellogg School of Management and Duke University’s Fuqua School of Business. He is a founding director and chairman of Macedonia 2025, an organization dedicated to enhancing the country’s economic and democracy development. He and his wife, Robin, are co-chairs and past national chairs for Duke University's Parents' Committee. Mike, Robin and their three sons Matt, Kirk and Todd are officers of the Zafirovski Family Foundation, formed in 2005 focusing on education and health issues.    Zafirovski holds a B.A. in mathematics from Edinboro University in Pennsylvania where he captained the intercollegiate soccer and swimming teams. In 2002, Edinboro University awarded him an honorary doctorate degree. A native of Macedonia, he received the Ellis Island Medal of Honor in 2004 and the Distinguished Leadership Award from the NY Hall of Science in 2008.ExperienceFounder, President/ CEOThe Zaf Group2012  –  Present (5 years)Executive AdvisorThe Blackstone Group2011  –  Present (6 years)Member of Board of DirectorsBoeing2004  –  Present (13 years)Non- Executive ChairmanDJO Global ( a Blackstone company)2012  –  Present (5 years)Non-Executive chairmanPolymer Group Inc (a Blackstone company)2012  –  Present (5 years)Member of Board of DirectorsStericycle2012  –  Present (5 years)Member of  Board of DirectorsApria Healthcare (a Blackstone company)2011  –  Present (6 years)President, CEO and Board MemberNortel Networks2006  –  2009 (3 years)President, CEO, Board Member, Office of ChairmanMotorola2002  –  2005 (3 years)President and CEO, Handset DivisionMotorola2000  –  2002 (2 years)President and CEOGE Lighting1999  –  2000 (1 year)President and CEOGE Lighting, EMEA1996  –  1999 (3 years)PresidentGE Mortgage Corporation1994  –  1996 (2 years)President and CEOGE Capital Fleet Services, EMEA1992  –  1994 (2 years)Brussels Area, BelgiumSVP- Finance, Marketing, Credit and BDGE Capital Fleet Services1989  –  1991 (2 years)President and CEOGE Capital Auto Auctions1986  –  1989 (3 years)SVP- BD and StrategyGE Capital Auto Financial Services1985  –  1986 (1 year)SVP- FinanceGE Capital Auto Finacial Services1984  –  1985 (1 year)Manager- Financial Planning and AnalysisGE Capital1981  –  1984 (3 years)Corporate AuditorGE1978  –  1981 (3 years)Financial Management ProgramGE1975  –  1978 (3 years)EducationEdinboro University of PennsylvaniaBachelor of Arts (B.A.), MathematicsBachelor of Arts (B.A.), Mathematics1971  –  1975Activities and Societies: Soccer